claim.claim-text:
1. A gas inlet manifold for a process chamber, comprising:
a chamber wall comprising a chamber top wall and a chamber side wall, wherein the chamber wall includes one or more one gas inlet passageways;
a showerhead including:
(i) an upward-facing surface and a downward-facing surface;
(ii) a plurality of gas outlet passageways extending between the upward-facing surface and the downward-facing surface; and
(iii) one or more grooves in the upward-facing surface, wherein the grooves are located between the gas outlet passageways and the perimeter of the upward-facing surface;

a suspension connected between the chamber wall and the showerhead so as to suspend the showerhead at a distance below the top wall; and
a gas sealing skirt including:
(i) an upper portion that is connected to the chamber wall, and
(ii) a lower portion that extends into one or more of said grooves and is not connected to the showerhead;

wherein the chamber wall, the showerhead and the gas sealing skirt collectively enclose a volume through which gas can flow from the gas inlet passageways to the gas outlet passageways.

5. The gas inlet manifold of claim 1, wherein:
the showerhead has a rectangular shape;
the suspension includes four flexible suspension walls such that each suspension wall is connected between the chamber wall and the showerhead;
the gas sealing skirt includes four sides; and
each side of the gas sealing skirt is flexible enough to bend radially outward by at least 0.5% of its horizontal width.

7. A method of enclosing a gas inlet plenum of a process chamber, comprising the steps of:
providing a chamber wall comprising a chamber top wall and a chamber side wall, wherein the chamber wall includes one or more gas inlet passageways;
providing a showerhead including:
(i) an upward-facing surface and a downward-facing surface;
(ii) a plurality of gas outlet passageways extending between the upward-facing surface and the downward-facing surface; and
(iii) one or more grooves in the upward-facing surface, wherein the grooves are located between the gas outlet passageways and the perimeter of the upward-facing surface;

connecting a suspension between the chamber wall and the showerhead so as to suspend the showerhead at a distance below the top wall;
positioning a gas sealing skirt so that the chamber wall, the showerhead and the gas sealing skirt collectively enclose a gas inlet plenum through which gas can flow from the gas inlet passageways to the gas outlet passageways;
connecting an upper portion of the gas sealing skirt to the chamber wall; and
positioning a lower portion of the gas sealing skirt so that it extends into one or more of said grooves and is not connected to the showerhead.

12. The method of claim 7, wherein:
the showerhead has a rectangular shape;
the suspension includes four flexible suspension walls such that each suspension wall is connected between the chamber wall and the showerhead;
the gas sealing skirt includes four sides; and
each side of the gas sealing skirt is flexible enough to bend radially outward by at least 0.5% of its horizontal width.

